Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags

Class ReverseIPTag

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags.Tag
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags.ReverseIPTag
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Tag>
public final class ReverseIPTag extends Tag
Used to hold data that is contained within a Reverse IP tag. Reverse IP tags allow data to flow at runtime from the outside world into SpiNNaker; they are the SpiNNaker equivalent of a server socket. Such packets must include an SDP header.

      public ReverseIPTag(InetAddress boardAddress, int tagID, int udpPort, HasCoreLocation destination, int sdpPort)
      Create a reverse IP tag.
      Parameters:
      boardAddress - The IP address of the board on which the tag is allocated.
      tagID - The tag of the SDP packet.
      udpPort - The UDP port on which SpiNNaker will listen for packets.
      destination - The coordinates of the core to send packets to.
      sdpPort - The port number to use for SDP packets that are formed on the machine.
